reviews.text: I enjoyed the freshness of the ingredients I ordered and I am happy with the choices too however they seem to be short staffed all the time and cannot provide good services.   Otherwise the restaurant is bright and ventilation is good enough to clear the bbq smoke and smell away.  Common to all retailers in HK space is at a premium so I find the tables are just too small.

Very good service from the manager. Would even thank you by your surname when you use a credit card to pay the bill. Food is alright, and the portions aren’t bad. Can be packed from time to time as it’s popular with students. Pricing is good value compared with other restaurants in the area.
Reasonable food, reasonable prices
Tasty food and good service.  Slightly pricey.
Went there for lunch but nothing close to Korean cuisine. Will not try again.

reviews.text: Lived here for 12 years. A quiet place with a nice sea view. I love watching the boats and ships in the sea. However, every time when there's a powerful typhoon, there's got to be some damage dealt to Heng Fa Chuen. But overall, this is a very good housing estate.
A very good community with a shopping mall linked with the MTR station. 😀
A self contained, quiet and pleasant living area.
Lived there for 9 years. Nice quiet estate close to MTR. Great for family with kids. Downside is it is very humid and for those blocks near the seaside were hit hard during typhoons.
lowkey good place for scuba diving during typhoon
